1. to generate cscope.out file recursively 
$ cscope -R

2. To use the already existing cscope.out file
$ cscope -d

3. To include the header, c and cpp file
$ touch tags.lst
$ find | grep "\.c$" >> tags.lst
$ find | grep "\.cpp$" >> tags.lst
$ find | grep "\.h$" >> tags.lst
$ cscope -i tags.lst
$ ctrl + z
$ cscope -d

4. to quit the cscope window
$ ctrl + z

